external_knowledge:
- Videos can have multiple ratings, and the average rating is calculated by summing all ratings and dividing by the number of ratings;
- The `COALESCE` function is used to handle cases where a video has no ratings, setting the average rating to 0;
- The results are ordered alphabetically by the video title.

sql:
SELECT MAX(total_views) AS highest_total_views
FROM (
    SELECT SUM(v.view_count) AS total_views
    FROM videos v
    GROUP BY v.author_id
) AS author_views;

