- High average watch time is defined as greater than 120 seconds;
- Popular among viewers means the video has been viewed by at least 100 unique users.

- 'resounded with the audience' refers to videos with a high number of views and a high rating;
- 'top 5 by the number of ratings' means the videos with the highest count of ratings in their category;
- 'average like rating' is calculated as the proportion of likes among all ratings.

- "crown jewel" refers to the highest or most valuable item in a collection;
- "kingdom of categories" refers to the set of all video categories;
- The query finds the highest average rating among all video categories.

sql:
SELECT video_id, AVG(rating) AS average_rating
FROM video_ratings
GROUP BY video_id;

